# Prevention Checklist: 

## ✅ Do’s:
- Use strong and unique passwords for all your accounts.
- Enable two-factor authentication (2FA) wherever possible.
- Think carefully before sharing personal information online.
- Adjust privacy settings on your social media accounts.
- Be respectful and responsible while posting or commenting.
- Verify links and messages before clicking or responding.
- Keep your devices updated with the latest security software.
- Talk to someone you trust if you face online harassment or threats.

## Financial/UPI Safety Tips:
- Never share your OTP or UPI PIN with anyone.
- Do not scan unknown QR codes or click on suspicious payment links.

## ❌ Don’ts:
- Do not respond to abusive or threatening messages.
- Avoid accepting friend requests from unknown people.
- Do not share sensitive information like bank details or passwords.
- Do not post anything that can harm your reputation or others.

## Reporting Channels:
- Report cybercrime at the National Cyber Crime Portal: https://cybercrime.gov.in
- Call the Cyber Crime Helpline: 1930
